<TITLE> Cabinet rejects pay rises for pres, PM, ministers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 14 (bdnews24.com)  The cabinet on Thursday rejected a proposal for increasing salaries of the president, ministers, state ministers and deputy ministers. It gave provisional approval of the Bangladesh Tourism Board Act 2010 for the development of the sector. A board will be formed under the new law. The tourism board will handle policy while the existing Bangladesh Parjatan Corporation will oversee tourism services. The draft of the International Long Distance Telecommunications Services Policy 2009 also got provisional approval by the cabinet. The cabinet also gave approval for changing the Bengali name of the ministry of livestock and fisheries from 'pashu sampad' (animal resources) to 'prani sampad' (bio resources). It also gave final approval to the Public Servants (retirement) (amendment) Act 2010, to extend the service age of freedom fighters by two years. The prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad briefed reporters after the cabinet meeting, chaired by the prime minister. He said the cabinet congratulated Hasina on her successful India tour. She was also congratulated for her receipt of Indira Gandhi peace prize, he said. b
